Kenya Pension Fund to Sell Stake in Bamburi, Business Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-09T05:22:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/kenya-pension-fund-to-sell-stake-in-bamburi-business-daily-says.html
The  National Social Security Fund ,
Kenya’s state-run pension company, will sell its 14 percent
stake in Lafarge SA’s Kenyan unit, Bamburi Cement Co., Nairobi-
based Business Daily said today.  NSSF, as the fund is known, said rising competition will
reduce Bamburi’s growth prospects, Business Daily reported
citing Alex Kazongo, head of the pension company, as saying.  Kazongo ceased to be a director of Bamburi on March 4.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  